create folder smart-expense-tracker 
create venv using below command 
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate     (if this command is not working and giving error then use below command and then run this command again)
Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass
venv\Scripts\activate


Smart-Expense-Tracker/
│
├── venv/                     ← ⚙️ Virtual environment (auto-created folder)
│   ├── Scripts/
│   ├── Lib/
│   └── ...
│
├── app.py                    ← 🧠 Your Flask main app file
├── requirements.txt           ← (Optional, for dependencies)
│
├── templates/                ← 🖼 HTML files yahan rahenge
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── login.html
│   └── register.html
│
└── static/                   ← 🎨 CSS, JS, images (optional but recommended)
    ├── style.css
    └── script.js


when created all the files and import all the libraries then make a requirements file using below command
pip freeze >requirements.txt

then moved to git part 
use below command one by one 
git init
git status 
git add --all      
git add .     (same as above one else write one by one for single file)
git commit -m "first commit"

after that we need to push code to github and there are two ways 
1.  using vscode if we have linked out account to github account
2.  using push commands and before that we need to create the repository on github check below 

🔗 2️⃣ Connect your local repo to GitHub

👉 Go to GitHub → create a new empty repository (example: Smart-Expense-Tracker).

Then copy the repo URL (example):
https://github.com/<your-username>/Smart-Expense-Tracker.git

Now connect it:
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/Smart-Expense-Tracker.git

⬆️ 3️⃣ Push your code to GitHub
git branch -M main       # Rename branch to 'main' (standard)
git push -u origin main  # Push all code to GitHub
✅ After this, your full project (including app.py, templates/, etc.) will be visible on GitHub.
🔁 4️⃣ Next Time (after changes)

If you make some edits later, use these 3 commands only:
git add .
git commit -m "Updated registration form and MySQL logic"
git push


